Git Session 1                   

$git -v 					- Git Version

$git help or git -h			- Showing Commands 

$git help config			- Its opening git Manual on Web

$pwd 						- Its Shows Current Working Directory

$cd d: or cd c: 			- To Change Drive 

$git init                   - The git init command is used to create a new Git repository.               

$git config --global 
user.name "Sachin Shinde"   - To Set user Name to Git Commits

$git config --global 
user.email "sachin@gmail.com"   - To Set user Email to Git Commits

$git config --global --list  - display all the global Git configuration settings on our system

$ls 							- This will list the files and directories in the current directory.

$ls -l                       - Displays detailed information about each file and directory (permissions, owner, size, modification date, etc.).

$ls -a						- ls -a (List All Files, Including Hidden Files)

$ls -la						- Combines both -l and -a to show a detailed list of all files, including hidden ones.

Admin@DESKTOP-7T8QQKJ MINGW64 /d/Sachin
$ ls -la
total 12
drwxr-xr-x 1 Admin 197121 0 Sep 15 13:01  ./
drwxr-xr-x 1 Admin 197121 0 Sep 15 13:38  ../
drwxr-xr-x 1 Admin 197121 0 Sep 14 18:36 'Git PDF'/
drwxr-xr-x 1 Admin 197121 0 Sep 15 13:03  git_projects/
drwxr-xr-x 1 Admin 197121 0 Sep 14 18:26  javascript_lectures/


this one dot is current directory
two dots are parent directory

$git status   				-to display the current state of the working directory and the staging area.

$git add						-In git to stage one file or track file use this

$git add --all				-In git to Stage Multiple files or Track files Use this


$git commit -m "message"     - This command creates a new commit in the repository, 
							  which takes all the changes in the staging area and records them as a new snapshot of the project.



touch file_name				- creates New file in Our directory
$ touch README.txt

nano 						- to Write in that file
$ nano README.txt

$ git log					- to display the commit history of a Git repository.

$ clear						- to Clear Terminal



git Session 2 

$ git remote add origin https://github.com/sachishindepatil/git-demo.git
							-adding remote repository


$git remote -v              -show remote repository


